  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpouse of the study is to determine wether Ultrasound Guided,Ens-assisted paravertebral
      block with single shot is a safe and reliable anesthetic technique in breast surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      General anaesthesia is currently the conventional technique used for breast surgery. Thoracic
      Paravertebral block (PVB) has been used with multiple injection.

      We compared a single injection thoracic PVB with general anaesthesia (GA) in 20 consenting
      patients, scheduled for unilateral breast surgery.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
